a="Happy Bdy"
puts a
o/p
Happy

puts a.upcase()
//prints in uppercase

puts a.downcase()
//prints in lowercase

puts a.length()
//prints the size

puts a.include? "Bdy"
//returns true if present in a

puts a[0]
//prints 1st char of a

puts a[0,3]
//prints from 0th index to 2nd 

puts a.index("H")
//returns the index of the char - here 0

We can also use it for strings directly:
puts "Heyy".upcase()


